 Financial Instruments 1.Commercial paper is short-term, discounted and unsecured corporate debt of large American banks and companies issued, usually for one to three months only, as way of borrowing money. 
金融財政儀器1.商業票據是短期,打折和無擔保的法人組織借款的廣大的美語銀行和公司發行,通常為了一到三月唯一,如同方法的借錢. 

2.Zero coupon bonds pay no interest, but are sold at a large discount and ultimately redeemed at face value. 
2.零息票結合償付不興趣,但是是賣在一廣大的打折和最終買回在面值. 

They consequently yield capital gains, often taxed at a lower rate than interest, which is considered as income. 
他們因此而被迫放棄首都利潤,常常稅在一較低的比例比興趣,哪個是考慮過如同收入. 

3.Detachable warrants are sometimes issued with bonds, and give the buyer the right to buy the same firm’s equities within a certain period. 
3 .可拆開授權是有時發行和結合,和給與買主這權力來買這相同堅固公平在範圍內一一定期間. 

Unlike convertible bonds, the bond itself is not converted into shares. 
不像可轉換的結合,這結合它自己不轉換到分配. 

4.Securitization is the process of selling packages of bank debts to third party investors as bonds. 
4 .是過程的銷售包裹的銀行借款到第三者投資者如同結合. 

It shifts the risk of default from the bank to the new owners, and releases capital with which the bank can make new loans. 
它改變這危險的不履行製造這銀行到這新船東,和釋放首都和哪個這銀行能以新借款. 

5.Junk bonds are high-yielding bonds issued by less secure companies and by companies seeking to finance leveraged buy-outs. 
5.廢物結合是高的-聽從結合發行以(經由)較少安全公司和以(經由)公司尋找到財政槓桿作用買-向外. 

6.A borrower with a lot of floating loans can spread the risk via an interest-rate swap with a borrower of fixed rate loans. 
6 .一借用人和許多的漂浮借款能伸展這危險經由利率交換和一借用人的修理好比例借款. 

7.An importer who will need foreign exchange in three or six months time can buy it in advance by way of a futures contract. 
7 .進口商誰將需要外匯在三或六月時間能買它預先經由一期貨合同. 

8.Banks can convert large deposits that cannot be withdrawn on demand into certificates of deposit short-term, interest-bearing securities that can be traded like a share or bond. 
8 .銀行能轉換廣大的存放那個不能撤退與 ,興趣-舉止安全那個有可能是交易喜歡一份或結合要求到證明文件的存放短的-. 

9.Debt swaps, letters of credit, options, etc. 
9.借款交換,文字的賒帳,選擇權,等等. 

are all forms of financial business that need not be registered as loans on a balance sheet. 
是全部表格的金融財政貿易那個毋庸是註冊的如同借款在一資產負債表. 

They are consequently known as off-balance-sheet transaction. 
他們是因此而知道如同離開-資產負債表辦理. 

10.Futures markets deal in contracts for standardized quantities of commodities, currencies, etc., for specific time periods. 
10.將來市場交易在契約為了標準化量的日用品,貨幣,等等.,為了指定時間期間. 

Non-standardized deals can be negotiated in an over-the –counter forward contract. 
非-標準化交易有可能是商議在在上-這–計數器期貨契約. 

11.Issuing participation certificates - which grant their holder part of the ownership of a company, but without voting rights- rather than shares, diminishes the risk of takeovers. 
11 .發行參與證明文件-哪個允許他們的持有者部份的所有權的一公司,但是沒有選舉右方-而非分配,減少這危險的取代. 

12.Two borrowers, each with a better credit rating in their own country, but also needing foreign currency, can arrange a currency swap. 
12.二借用人,每個和一更好賒帳等級在他們自己的國家,而且需要外幣,能整理一貨幣交換.





