Shiuhansen has done a great work. Thanks.There are around 30 stock options listing on the Taiwan Futures Exchange. The underlying stocks of these options are all heavy-weighted blue chips, such as Formosa Plastic, China Steel, Evergreen Marine, UMC, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC), Cathay Financial Holdings, etc. However, the daily turnovers of these options are usually very light because of their settlement limitation and poor design. It seems that only options market makers, who are responsible for providing price quotations, do some trades from time to time. On the other hand, the index options of Taiwan Futures Exchange are very popular as they are convenient for settlement and trade. There are lots of stock warrants, issued by different securities firms, listing on Taiwan Stock Exchange as well. Basically, these stock warrants are the same as stock options in nature. Local retail investors used to trade these warrants actively 4-6 years ago. These warrants have become less and less attractive since investors realize that they can not beat those issuers over the long run.


    	    	
